{"ts":"2026-07-03T14:54:15.551Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-4i73"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"Test meaningfulness audit: strengthen hollow assertions, de-mock thin specs, convert contract source-mirrors to behavior"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":"Four-way audit of the 263-spec suite for hollow/tautological/over-mocked tests, followed by remediation on feat/extreme-quality-gates. Verified live: coverage 100/100/100/100 (32772/32772 stmts), 5312 tests green, jscpd 0 clones incl. tests, pragma budget 498/498 burn-down."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Task"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"in_progress"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":2},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["quality","tests"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-07-03T14:54:15.551Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-03T14:54:15.551Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"maintainer-agent"}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"c148cb45337d5df837c2bf2d87d07f1b78fe61d46d080eb74884e8ab1ab4f7da","message":""}
{"ts":"2026-07-03T14:54:32.883Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"note_add","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-03T14:54:32.883Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/notes","value":[{"created_at":"2026-07-03T14:54:32.882Z","author":"maintainer-agent","text":"Audit findings (4 parallel reviews, worst first):\n1. release-automation-contract.spec.ts — 4 tests assert exact SOURCE SUBSTRINGS of scripts (bundle-cli lock internals, telemetry gate literals, Sentry query signature, release-notes date lines) instead of behavior; brittle to refactors, blind to semantic regressions.\n2. ci-workflow-contract.spec.ts:75-220 — ~90-line verbatim mirror of ci.yml (step names, full cache keys byte-for-byte); change-detector, not a contract. Keep: SHA-pin regexes, no-publish negative checks, 120-file cap.\n3. cli-main-errors.spec.ts:281-284 — setRecoveredExtensionServices tested with bare not.toThrow(); a no-op body would pass. Effect observable via runActiveServiceOverrideSync.\n4. stats-command.spec.ts:303-323 — title claims tag-prefix filtering is tested; only 4x toBeDefined, prefix never asserted.\n5. restore-command.spec.ts:546/561/576 — rollback tests use rejects.toBeTruthy(); early NOT_FOUND rejection makes rollback assertions vacuous.\n6. Over-mocked thin specs: invalidate-search-caches.spec.ts (condition AND effect mocked), list-sort-branches.spec.ts (whole store virtualized), search-command.spec.ts on-read-hook block (asserts only against mocked extensions module).\n7. Scattered: rejects.toBeDefined() where ENOENT/EACCES should be pinned (telemetry-consent, item-format-migration, search-cache, telemetry-runtime, cli.integration, todos-extension); register-commands else-path block with 1 bare toHaveBeenCalled for 12 dispatches; smoke-cleanup mock-fs not.toThrow-only; package-manifest regex-parses source instead of importing.\nCleared: no tautological mock-asserting-mock anywhere; 82 specs use real temp FS; integration layer (31 specs, zero vi.mock) runs the built CLI with exit-code/stdout/FS assertions; ~80% of toBeDefined hits are TS narrowing followed by real assertions; coverage pragmas (498) all justified defensive/unreachable with budget frozen.\nRemediation running as 4 parallel fix agents with disjoint file ownership; gates to re-verify after: coverage 100x4, eslint 0 warnings, jscpd 0 clones."}]}],"before_hash":"c148cb45337d5df837c2bf2d87d07f1b78fe61d46d080eb74884e8ab1ab4f7da","after_hash":"438e69cf80d520c82d05cea4befd3dd47709644f9f65f8b580230446ab3a712c"}
{"ts":"2026-07-03T14:54:50.692Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"learning_add","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-03T14:54:50.692Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/learnings","value":[{"created_at":"2026-07-03T14:54:50.691Z","author":"maintainer-agent","text":"Contract-spec antipattern: asserting exact source substrings (toContain on implementation code/YAML) mirrors the implementation instead of pinning behavior — passes rename-blind on real regressions, breaks on harmless refactors, and trains copy-paste test edits. Convert to executed-behavior tests (run script with --json + fixtures) or parsed-structure invariants (YAML job/matrix/SHA-pin checks)."}]}],"before_hash":"438e69cf80d520c82d05cea4befd3dd47709644f9f65f8b580230446ab3a712c","after_hash":"b2676107948cad4dd14baa2358d56429d97076fd894e7d979caba2908b8a4d1f"}
{"ts":"2026-07-03T14:54:51.153Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"learning_add","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/learnings/1","value":{"created_at":"2026-07-03T14:54:51.152Z","author":"maintainer-agent","text":"Grep counts of toBeDefined()/not.toThrow() overstate hollowness ~5x: in this suite ~80% were TypeScript narrowing guards immediately followed by exact assertions, or legitimate accept-path contracts paired with exact-message throw tests. Judge each hit against the source under test before flagging."}},{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-03T14:54:51.153Z"}],"before_hash":"b2676107948cad4dd14baa2358d56429d97076fd894e7d979caba2908b8a4d1f","after_hash":"b6e8d2a53407137654cd451e51f5dfe4d6926d4700861f1b718fc683369172c4"}
{"ts":"2026-07-03T14:54:51.764Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"learning_add","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/learnings/2","value":{"created_at":"2026-07-03T14:54:51.764Z","author":"maintainer-agent","text":"100%-coverage gates breed two artifacts to watch for: (1) coverage-marking test blocks that invoke many branches with a single bare toHaveBeenCalled(), and (2) _testOnly seams testing runtime-unreachable defensive branches. Fix (1) by pinning per-call args; (2) is acceptable when the branch is a real drift guard, since the pragma budget (498, burn-down-only) forbids new ignore pragmas."}},{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-03T14:54:51.764Z"}],"before_hash":"b6e8d2a53407137654cd451e51f5dfe4d6926d4700861f1b718fc683369172c4","after_hash":"858ccedbabc3494a62962f24492199c12b0eee16d22078137df624ed12446529"}
{"ts":"2026-07-03T14:54:52.330Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"learning_add","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/learnings/3","value":{"created_at":"2026-07-03T14:54:52.329Z","author":"maintainer-agent","text":"Mock-audit rubric that worked: classify every vi.mock as boundary (child_process/fetch/TTY/SDK/clock = fine), first-party-replacement (suspect: test passes with broken impl), or mock-asserting-mock (tautological). House style of withTempPmPath real-FS workspaces plus fake-transport-at-the-boundary (e.g. fake git writing real trees) is why this suite audited clean."}},{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-03T14:54:52.330Z"}],"before_hash":"858ccedbabc3494a62962f24492199c12b0eee16d22078137df624ed12446529","after_hash":"1bc0fa11bda50ac3870e0a8e84e38448cf891500f040b5bcda7a92a977a2c485"}
{"ts":"2026-07-03T14:54:52.914Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"learning_add","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/learnings/4","value":{"created_at":"2026-07-03T14:54:52.911Z","author":"maintainer-agent","text":"rejects.toBeDefined()/toBeTruthy() on fs promises is a vacuous-pass hazard: any rejection (typo'd path, EACCES, early usage error) satisfies it. Pin rejects.toMatchObject({ code: \"ENOENT\" | \"EACCES\" }) — and for rollback tests, pin the error to the induced failure point so an early rejection can't fake a successful rollback."}},{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-03T14:54:52.914Z"}],"before_hash":"1bc0fa11bda50ac3870e0a8e84e38448cf891500f040b5bcda7a92a977a2c485","after_hash":"eb7cde2aafad07c7f01603b6e7e91150b5e7d2227c6e7a6c7ba155cc347054cd"}
